# Change Workflow

- After each completed code or configuration change, rebuild Docker so the latest app can be tested.
- Use the repository's existing Docker workflow when possible; prefer `docker compose build` unless a more specific project command is clearly established.
- Use `sudo` when needed to complete approved project maintenance tasks, such as Docker rebuilds or dependency installation.
- Install software as needed when it is required to complete the user's requested project work.
- Do not store passwords, tokens, or other secrets in committed files, including Cursor rules.
- After each completed change, commit the full intended change set and push it to `main`.
- If a build, commit, or push is blocked by the local environment or permissions, report the blocker clearly and leave the repository in the safest completed state.
